    "summary": "Augmentir publicly describes rich APIs, oData support, standard connectors, asset hierarchy management, workflow building, forms, maintenance notifications, and enterprise integrations for connected-worker operations.",
    "description": "Manufactured OpenAPI artifact for Augmentir integrations/API. This file was synthesized by Last Mile from curated research JSON and is not vendor-certified. Use it as an agent-consumable starting point, then validate paths, schemas, authentication, and server URLs with the vendor before production use. Augmentir's public product pages describe an AI-native connected worker platform with no-code workflow building, smart forms, issue management, asset hierarchy management, and extensibility through rich APIs, oData, pro-code extensibility, and standard enterprise connectors. The public integration content highlights bi-directional integration with ERP, CMMS, QMS, MES, CRM, HCM, and LMS systems, plus asset-centered work and maintenance procedures, skills requirements, collaboration, associated documentation, CIL or standard work schedules, and history of activities on each asset. This is a write-capable manufacturing workflow platform with supported asset-oriented data, but it does not present public telemetry APIs. Asset data is Supported. Telemetry data is Unsupported. Writeback is Supported.",
